commit.message:
Fix: Info manual generation

GNU ELPA's build process complained that:

  Manual name "README.html" conflicts with "activities/README.html"

So this implements the same pattern used in activities.el's readme,
which works on ELPA.

Fix: Handle HTTP 303 redirects

Fixes <https://github.com/alphapapa/org-web-tools/issues/67>.

Reported-by: Daniel Hubmann <https://github.com/hubisan>
Tests: Tidy with local URL function

Tests: Update commentary

Since the bug mentioned seems to be solved in v0.7, I suppose the
explanation can be removed now!
Meta: Update copyright year in tests

Tidy: Docstrings

To satisfy checkdoc's using a default dictionary which doesn't seem to
have words like "enqueue" and "prepend", we hyphenate or avoid them.

Fix: (plz-clear) Only kill live processes

Don't try to kill a process that has already finished.

Fix: (plz) Use with-local-quit for synchronous requests

Fixes <https://github.com/alphapapa/plz.el/issues/26>.

Tests: Unwrap (and (should ...) ...)

SHOULDs shouldn't be inside ANDs.

Also, use map-nested-elt.
